    "(a) Using the first element of the encoder output, corresponding to the CLS token.",
    "As explained in Section 4, the motivation behind this approach is that pre-training of BERT on next-sentence prediction tasks uses the encoder output corresponding to the CLS token as input to the prediction.",
    "(b) Mean pooling, i.e.",
    "averaging over the encodings of all sequence items (except those items which are used to pad the sequence to a minimum length).",
    "Note that the transformer encoder and its self-attention mechanism do have a sense of word ordering."
